Multi Node Setup
----------------

Bridge Adaptor - Local + Interenet connection
NAT  Adaptor - Interenet connection
Host Only Adaptor - Local connection


On Master
Kube API Server is required
Docker Engine
Kublet program

DB - Service
etcd is a distributed key-value store.
In fact, etcd is the primary datastore of Kubernetes;
storing and replicating all Kubernetes cluster state.
As a critical component of a Kubernetes cluster having
a reliable automated approach to its configuration and management is imperative.

For Master/Slave
[Refer- https://kubernetes.io/docs/setup/production-environment/tools/kubeadm/create-cluster-kubeadm/]
1. We need OS
2. Yum needs to be configured
3. Need docker
4. Kubelet
5. Minikube/EKS/kuveadm
6. Firewall - disabled
7. Disable SELinux - setenforce 0
8. Change cgroup to systemctld
9. Disable cgroup

